preamble: Tendrils makes use of the open source libraries listed below.

cargo-dependencies.name: aho-corasick
cargo-dependencies.desc: Fast multiple substring searching.

cargo-dependencies.name: ansi-str
cargo-dependencies.desc: A library which provides a set of methods to work with ANSI strings

cargo-dependencies.name: ansitok
cargo-dependencies.desc: A library for parsing ANSI Escape Codes

cargo-dependencies.name: anstream
cargo-dependencies.desc: A simple cross platform library for writing colored text to a terminal.

cargo-dependencies.name: arrayvec

cargo-dependencies.name: autocfg
cargo-dependencies.desc: Automatic cfg for Rust compiler features

cargo-dependencies.name: bitflags

cargo-dependencies.desc:
A macro to ergonomically define an item depending on a large number of #[cfg]
parameters. Structured like an if-else chain, the first matching branch is the
item that gets emitted.
